A new day, a new horror story of independence.
This time we are warned that an independent Scotland is needed to join the Schengen area as a prerequisite for EU membership.
This provides the keyword for stories about passport controls in Berwick and a barbed wire-backed border along the Hadrian’s Wall.
Indeed, the Strathclyde template highlighted the potential economic benefits that would bring more freedom of travel in the rest of Europe, but this did not play a role in the headlines, as expected.
