Jack Valero of Catholic Voices said that the number of electoral cardinals is likely to have decreased by February.
He explained that a pope usually appoints as many cardinals as necessary so that the number of cardinals eligible to vote again amounts to 120, and as many cardinals over 80 as he wishes.
The Consistory next year is significant because it is the first since the election of Francis in March this year, Valero said.
